AB  - We take issue with Angelini's (1994) claim that the founding of the Federal Reserve was not responsible for a change in the stochastic process followed by short-term interest rates. We argue that Angelini's failure to reject the null hypothesis of no regime change around the date of the founding of the Fed is due to the low power of his test.
